        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 5:35PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 535 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Red Bank, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Bank, Gaston, Pelion, Thor, Lexington County Airport At Pelion,
Lexington Acres Pond, Steedman, Samaria Fire Station, Peachtree Rock,
Red Bank Sports Complex, Edmund, and Cedar Pond Campground.

This includes Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 38
and 53.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
